Class NoGUI

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.uvigo.esei.ephyslab.fortrananalyser.NoGUI

  • public class NoGUI
extends Object
    This class create a NoGUI and support the logic part of the application without graphical intercface, after that it generate the quallity report.

    1.9.2
    Author:

      • analyseGoodComment

        private String analyseGoodComment(String filePath)
                           throws IOException
        This method check if all comments are good. This is: 1.- the functions are commented after or before the declaration. 2.- the variables are commented after or before the declaration. 3.- the subrutines are commented after or befor the declaration. 4.- the three first or more lines of a file are commented.
        Parameters:
        filePath - of the file analysed
        Returns:
        the paragraph to add to the pdf file
        Throws:
        IOException - in case something wrong with intput/output file

        Returns:

      • analyseGoodCommentedVariables

        private boolean analyseGoodCommentedVariables(String filePath)

      • analyseGoodCommentFunctions

        private boolean analyseGoodCommentFunctions(String filePath)
                                     throws IOException
        This method check if the functions delcared in a file have or not have a comment. The comment can be after or before the declaration of the function. In addition, at the end of functions there are no comments.
        Parameters:
        filePath - of the analysed file
        Returns:
        boolean with the result of the use of good comments in functions
        Throws:
        IOException - in case something wrong with intput/output file
